  "State Snell's Law.": "",
  "n₁/sin θ₁ = n₂/sin θ₂": "",
  "n₁ θ₁ = n₂ θ₂": "",
  "n₁ sin θ₁ = n₂ sin θ₂": "",
  "n₁ cos θ₁ = n₂ cos θ₂": "",
  "Snell's Law: n₁sin(θ₁) = n₂sin(θ₂). Light bends toward the normal when entering a denser medium (higher index of refraction) and away from normal when entering a less dense medium. The answer is 'n₁ sin θ₁ = n₂ sin θ₂'. The other options — 'n₁ cos θ₁ = n₂ cos θ₂', 'n₁ θ₁ = n₂ θ₂', and 'n₁/sin θ₁ = n₂/sin θ₂' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": "",
