  "The point where light stops traveling and is completely absorbed": "",
  "The region inside a lens where light rays converge together": "",
  "The maximum distance that light can travel through a material": "",
  "An optical boundary is the surface or interface where two different media meet. When light strikes this boundary, it can be reflected, refracted, or both, depending on the angle and the media involved.": "",
  "A student shines a flashlight into a swimming pool at an angle. The light beam appears to bend as it enters the water. Why does this happen?": "",
