  "In a physics lab, a student shines light from air into glass (n = 1.5) at 30° to the normal. What happens to the angle of refraction?": "",
  "The refracted angle is exactly 30° because light does not bend": "",
  "The refracted angle is larger than 30° inside the glass block": "",
  "The refracted angle is smaller than 30° inside the glass block": "",
  "The refracted angle equals 60° because the angles always add up": "",
  "When light enters a denser medium (glass, n = 1.5), it slows down and bends toward the normal. By Snell's Law, sin θ₂ = (n₁/n₂) sin θ₁ = (1/1.5) sin 30° = 0.333, so θ₂ ≈ 19.5°, which is less than 30°.": "",
